$interpreted: Tingko: Ji... Jihasaha?
Jihasaha: Did I ask you my name?
Tingko: Crap! Get over here, quick!
Jihasaha: What?
Tingko: ...Good, no one followed.
Tingko: Thank you for your help, but... You know who I am. Why would you help me?
Jihasaha: What's wrong with you, letting people slander the princess like that?
Tingko: I... I didn't mean to...
Jihasaha: I don't need excuses from weaklings. Just tell me why you're here, and not the princess.
Tingko: Well, it's because...
Tingko: Didn't you hear? The princess isn't well enough to see you this time!
Jihasaha: So what? I didn't hear it from her personally. Plus, if she's sick it's my official duty to make sure she's all right.
Tingko: It's not like you're a general or something, what do you care about duty?
Tingko: The princess is sick, and she should rest. If you want to see her, you can do it in a few days when you come back to get her reply.
Jihasaha: I wouldn't feel right.
Tingko: Please, we're taking care of her. She'll be fine.
Jihasaha: That's exactly why I'm worried.
Jihasaha: From what I've seen of you before, I have reason to doubt your abilities as a caretaker.
Tingko: What gives you the right to say that!?
Jihasaha: Like just now. If I didn't show up, what would have happened to you? Would you have yelled him to death?
Tingko: ......
Jihasaha: If you were any good at watching over her, then she wouldn't be sick in the first place. What makes you think she'll get better?
Jihasaha: If you understand, then you'll step aside.
Tingko: Ugh, you're such a... just don't bother her for too long.
Cranky Guard: Who goes there!?
Tingko: I am Princess Tindoiimu's servant. I've already reported my leave this morning...
Cranky Guard: I'm talking about this punk.
Tingko: He's Jihasaha, he's been here before...
Cranky Guard: Jiha-say what? Never heard of him. I've only heard of the Royal Horn.
Tingko: Yeah, that's him...
Jihasaha: Out with it, what do you want? This isn't the first time.
Cranky Guard: I heard the Royal Horn is really something. If you're him, then you should be able to subdue these beasts without layin' a finger on 'em.
Tingko: Hold on... what does this have to do with anything?
Jihasaha: Fine, if that's what you want.
Cranky Guard: Wha... how!?
Jihasaha: You happy?
Cranky Guard: Wa... you really did it...
Tingko: Bet you believe him now!
Cranky Guard: Yeah... alright, get going.
Jiyanama: Tingko! Didn't we say he shouldn't come today?
Tingko: I told him, but he didn't listen!
Jiyanama: Even so, you can't just...
Tindoiimu: Nana, don't blame Tingko. I figured this would happen.
Jihasaha: I had to see you, princess.
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, you're such a pest!
Jihasaha: I heard you were sick, I was worried.
Tindoiimu: Well, here I am.
Jihasaha: You seem okay. You're a tough one.
Tindoiimu: You're hurt... did the guards make trouble with you again?
Jihasaha: Oh, this? Don't worry, barely a scratch.
Tindoiimu: You don't need to get hurt just to see me. If you're not careful you might find yourself in real trouble.
Jihasaha: Hmph... Seems to me like it's not only physical weakness that's gotten you sick.
Jihasaha: I think you've been a hostage for too long. Clinging to some phony idea of "peace"... It's gotten you scared of your own shadow.
Tingko: That's enough!
Tingko: The princess is worried about you. Can't you just have some empathy!?
Jihasaha: Worried? Empathy? The enemy doesn't care about those things. Those emotions will just get you killed.
Tingko: The princess isn't weak. It's because she understands these emotions that she's stronger than you'll ever be.
Jihasaha: Because the princess has to constantly watch after brats like you.
Tindoiimu: Alright, enough...
Jihasaha: Forgive me, princess. I was too worked up... But, apart from standing around by your side, has she really helped you with anything?
Tingko: Well... what about you? The princess has been here, suffering, but where have you been? What have you been doing?
Tindoiimu: Enough—Ugh!!
Jihasaha: She's burning up!
Tingko: Jiyanama, get the medicine!
Jiyanama: ...The princess seems okay. Let her rest.

Jihasaha: I'm leaving.... 
Tingko, remember why you're here. Take care of the princess.
Tingko: ......
